				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In some architectures, like 6502, PowerPC and ARM, subtraction clears the carry flag if a borrow occurs and sets it if no borrow occurs. In other architectures like Intel, 6800 and 68000, the carry flag is set if a borrow occurs and cleared if no borrow occurs. The Game Boy CPU is Intel-derived and works the latter way.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

